<TITLE> Moriarty confirmed as US ambassador to Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 16 (bdnews24.com)The US Senate has confirmed the appointment of James Francis Moriarty as the next US ambassador to Bangladesh, the US embassy said in a statement Sunday. Moriarty, a native of Massachusetts and career member of the US senior foreign service, is expected to join his post in the "near future", said the statement. The post of US ambassador in Dhaka has been vacant since the immediate-past ambassador Patricia A Butenis left her assignment in June 2007 for a posting to the US embassy in Baghdad. Butenis had proved to be a much-talked-about envoy in Bangladesh for her frequent meetings with political leaders and frank discussions on the internal politics of the country. Moriarty's previous assignment was in Nepal as US ambassador. bdn
